    "bio": "Jamieson Greer is a trade lawyer who served as Chief of Staff to U.S. Trade Representative Robert Lighthizer during Trump's first term, helping design and implement the Section 301 tariffs on China. Confirmed 56-43 as U.S. Trade Representative in 2025, he has overseen implementation of Trump's sweeping \"Liberation Day\" tariffs announced in April 2025, a 10% baseline tariff on all imports and higher rates for specific countries, and subsequent trade negotiations. He is widely regarded as one of the most technically competent of Trump's second-term appointees.",
    "cabinet_industry": "Trade law / Government (USTR Chief of Staff 2017-2021)",
    "cabinet_conflicts": [
      "Liberation Day tariffs he implemented faced legal challenges, courts questioned whether executive branch could impose tariffs unilaterally without congressional authorization",
      "Trade policy affects trillions in commerce, past law firm clients in trade-affected industries raised potential conflicts",
      "One of few Trump nominees with broad bipartisan respect for technical competence (56-43 confirmation)"
    ]
  },
